recalls.Summary: Lamborghini (Automobili Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2018-2021 Huracan vehicles.  In temperatures below 41°F, the rearview camera may not display due to a software error in the infotainment system.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 111, "Rear Visibility."
recalls.Consequence: A rearview camera that does not display an image reduces the driver's rear view, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the instrument cluster software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on August 6, 2021.  Owners may contact Lamborghini customer service at 1-866-681-6276.  Lamborghini's number for this recall is L62X-R.01.21.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Lamborghini (Automobili Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2020-2022 Huracan EVO and 2022 Huracan STO vehicles.  The gearbox may have an insufficient amount of transmission oil, which can lead to clutch slippage, and in certain driving situations, a transmission oil leak.
recalls.Consequence: Clutch slippage can cause a loss of drive power and increase the risk of a crash.  A transmission oil leak in the presence of hot exhaust components can increase the risk of fire.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and correct the transmission oil level, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed May 20, 2022.  Owners may contact Automobili Lamborghini customer service 1-866-681-6276.  Automobili Lamborghini's number for this recall is L62X-R.02.22.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Lamborghini (Automobili Lamborghini) is recalling certain 2015-2024 Huracan vehicles.  The headlights may be incorrectly adjusted.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: Incorrectly adjusted headlights can reduce the visibility of oncoming traffic, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the software to deactivate the headlight functions for Tourist Mode and the Adaptive Front-lighting System (AFS), free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed February 6, 2024.  Owners may contact Lamborghini customer service at 1-866-681-6276.  Lamborghini's number for this recall is L62X-R.01.24.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Body Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber body panels, particularly rear wing elements and side panels, experience delamination where the carbon fiber layers separate, especially under extreme heat or track use conditions.
symptoms: Visible separation of carbon fiber layers
Bubbling or peeling of clear coat
issues.fix_description: Replace affected carbon fiber panels with updated parts. Lamborghini has issued revised manufacturing processes for newer panels.
issues.prevention: Avoid prolonged exposure to extreme heat, use covered parking, limit extended track sessions without cool-down periods

issues.title: Track-Focused Suspension Component Premature Wear
issues.description: The ultra-stiff track-oriented suspension components, including bushings and ball joints, wear faster than expected during street driving due to the aggressive setup.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn suspension components with updated parts. Some owners opt for slightly less aggressive bushings for street use.
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive driving on poor road surfaces, regular suspension inspections, consider softer bushings for street-only use

issues.title: Brake System Overheating on Track
issues.description: Despite the track-focused design, the brake system can overheat during extended track sessions, leading to brake fade and potential damage to brake components.
issues.fix_description: Upgrade brake pads to more aggressive compounds, install additional cooling ducts, replace brake fluid with higher temperature rated fluid.
issues.prevention: Use proper cool-down laps, upgrade to track-specific brake pads and fluid, install brake cooling modifications

issues.title: Aerodynamic Package Alignment Issues
issues.description: The large rear wing and front splitter can become misaligned due to mounting hardware loosening or minor impacts, affecting aerodynamic performance.
issues.fix_description: Realign aerodynamic components and retorque mounting hardware to specification. Replace any damaged mounting points.
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of aero components, careful driving over speed bumps and steep inclines, periodic retorquing of hardware

issues.title: Engine Oil Temperature Management
issues.description: The high-performance V10 engine can experience elevated oil temperatures during spirited driving or track use, potentially leading to oil degradation and engine protection activation.
issues.fix_description: Install additional oil cooling capacity, use higher grade synthetic oil, ensure proper oil levels and change intervals.
issues.prevention: Use recommended high-performance oil, avoid prolonged high-RPM operation without cool-down, monitor oil temperatures during track use

issues.title: Tire Wear Pattern Issues
issues.description: The aggressive alignment settings and track-focused suspension geometry cause uneven tire wear patterns, particularly on the edges of front tires during street driving.
symptoms: Rapid edge wear on front tires
issues.fix_description: Adjust alignment settings for street use if primarily driven on roads, rotate tires more frequently, consider different tire compounds.
issues.prevention: Regular tire rotation, alignment adjustments based on use case, avoid aggressive cornering on cold tires

issues.title: Electronic System Glitches
issues.description: Various electronic systems including the infotainment, telemetry, and driver assistance features experience intermittent glitches and software issues.
issues.fix_description: Software updates and occasional module replacements. Most issues resolved through dealer software updates.
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid system overload by limiting simultaneous functions, regular dealer service checks

issues.title: Paint and Clear Coat Durability
issues.description: Paint finish and clear coat show premature wear and damage from debris due to the low ride height and track-focused nature of the vehicle.
issues.fix_description: Paint protection film installation, touch-up paint work, clear coat polishing and protection treatments.
issues.prevention: Install paint protection film, avoid following vehicles closely, use car cover when parked, regular washing and waxing

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock
issues.description: During extended high-performance driving or in hot weather conditions, the fuel system can experience vapor lock issues affecting fuel delivery and engine performance.
issues.fix_description: Fuel system cooling improvements, fuel pump updates, and revised fuel line routing to minimize heat exposure.
issues.prevention: Allow proper cool-down periods, avoid topping off fuel tank, use high-quality fuel, minimize extended high-RPM operation in hot weather

editorial.hero_blurb: The Huracán STO strips away luxury for pure performance, delivering a road-going race car experience that prioritizes track capability over comfort. This is Lamborghini's most hardcore naturally aspirated V10, engineered for those who demand uncompromising performance.
editorial.essence: The STO represents the pinnacle of Lamborghini's naturally aspirated V10 evolution, combining motorsport-derived aerodynamics with a chassis tuned for maximum attack. It's a street-legal race car that makes no apologies for its singular focus on performance over practicality.
editorial.heritage: Born from Lamborghini's Super Trofeo racing program, the STO (Super Trofeo Omologata) transfers decades of motorsport knowledge into a road car. It represents the culmination of the Huracán lineage, incorporating lessons learned from both GT3 racing and the track-only SCV12.
editorial.design_philosophy: Every design element serves aerodynamic efficiency and weight reduction, from the massive rear wing to the aggressive front splitter. The STO abandons traditional Lamborghini luxury in favor of raw functionality, with carbon fiber construction and race-inspired aesthetics throughout.
editorial.motorsport_history: Directly derived from Lamborghini's Super Trofeo one-make racing series and influenced by the Huracán GT3 EVO program. The STO incorporates active aerodynamics and suspension tuning developed through countless hours of circuit testing.
editorial.engine_character: The 5.2L V10 delivers relentless, linear power with a spine-tingling crescendo that builds to an 8,500 RPM climax. This naturally aspirated masterpiece provides immediate throttle response and an intoxicating mechanical symphony that modern turbocharged engines simply cannot match.
editorial.transmission_feel: The seven-speed dual-clutch transmission snaps through gears with race-car precision, offering lightning-fast shifts in Corsa mode while remaining manageable in street driving. Paddle shifters provide direct connection to the drivetrain's aggressive character.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The STO's chassis is uncompromisingly stiff and track-focused, with adaptive dampers that can transform from brutal track tool to merely firm street machine. Body roll is virtually nonexistent, and the car changes direction with supernatural precision.
editorial.steering_feel: The electro-mechanical steering system provides immediate, unfiltered feedback with perfect weight distribution. Turn-in is razor-sharp with minimal lag between input and response, though it can feel twitchy at low speeds on uneven surfaces.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon-ceramic brakes provide phenomenal stopping power with excellent pedal feel and fade resistance. The system inspires complete confidence during aggressive track driving, though they can be grabby during gentle street use until warmed.
editorial.sound_signature: The naturally aspirated V10 produces an otherworldly howl that builds from a menacing growl to a screaming banshee wail. The exhaust note is pure mechanical poetry, with sharp pops and crackles on overrun that announce the car's presence blocks away.
editorial.ideal_owner: Track day enthusiasts and collectors who prioritize pure performance over comfort, with the skill to exploit the STO's capabilities and the passion to appreciate its uncompromising nature.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily drivers seeking comfort, buyers wanting practical luxury, or those intimidated by aggressive, unfiltered performance characteristics.
editorial.buyers_summary: The STO demands respect and rewards skill with an uncompromising track-focused experience that few street cars can match. This is a weekend warrior's dream machine, but only for those ready to embrace its hardcore nature and accept the comfort compromises.
